<section xml:id="linked-lists_vocabulary"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vocabulary</title>
  <p>
    <dl>
      <li>
        <title>doubly linked list:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>doubly linked list</h>
          </idx> A data structure consisting of a sequence of nodes, where each node contains data and references to both the next and previous nodes in the sequence.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>linked list:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>linked list</h>
          </idx> A data structure consisting of a sequence of nodes, where each node contains data and the nodes are connected via pointers. May be singly linked or doubly linked.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>head:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>head</h>
          </idx> The first node in a linked list.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>list:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>list</h>
          </idx> An abstract data type that represents a sequence of elements, where each element has a position in the sequence.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>list node:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>list node</h>
          </idx> A structure that contains data and the address of (a pointer to) the next node in the list.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>singly linked list:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>singly linked list</h>
          </idx> A data structure consisting of a sequence of nodes, where each node contains data and a reference to the next node in the sequence.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>tail:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>tail</h>
          </idx> The last node in a linked list.</p>
      </li>
    </dl>
  </p>
</section>